==Old English==
===Etymology===
Common Germanic: cognate with Old Frisian ''sīa'', Old High German [[sehan]] (German [[sehen]]), Old Saxon [[sehan]] (Dutch [[zien]]), Old Norse ''sjā'' (Swedish [[se]]), Gothic [[𐍃𐌰𐌹𐍈𐌰𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /se:on/

===Verb===
'''sēon''' (strong verb class V: '''siehþ'''/'''sihþ''' ‘he sees’; '''seah''' ‘he saw’; '''sāwon''' ‘they saw’; '''ġesewen''' ‘seen’)
# to [[see]]

